<div id="node-248" class="node node-type-story node-promoted node-teaser build-mode-teaser"><div class="node-inner">

  
      <h2 class="title">
      <a href="/node/248" title="Article: POJO Aspects in Spring 2.0: A Simple Example">Article: POJO Aspects in Spring 2.0: A Simple Example</a>
    </h2>
  
  
      <div class="meta">
              <div class="submitted">
          Submitted by Colin Sampaleanu on Sat, 2006-04-01 13:06        </div>
      
              <div class="terms terms-inline"> in <ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_6 first last active"><a href="/presentations" rel="tag" title="A link to a technical article about Spring" class="active">Technical Article</a></li>
</ul></div>
          </div>
  
  <div class="content">
    <p>In <a href="http://blog.springframework.com/markf/archives/2006/03/22/pojo-aspects-in-spring-20-a-simple-example/" target="_self">POJO Aspects in Spring 2.0: A Simple Example</a>, Mark Fisher describes some of the new AOP functionality in Spring 2.0, including the new &lt;aop:xxx&gt; XML namespace, and the use of aspects defined as POJOs (plain java objects).</p>
  </div>

